The address from the National Command Council and the social cluster briefing on socio-economic interventions under Level 3 conditions have both been postponed. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Two major briefings have been postponed on Wednesday. The National Coronavirus Command Council's briefing for this afternoon on the regulations to be implemented under Level 3 lockdown has been postponed. READ: SA will move to Level 3 from 1 June: Ramaphosa On Sunday, President Cyril Ramaphosa announced that the whole of the country would move to Level 3 from next week. The social cluster briefing on socio-economic interventions for Level 3 restrictions was also going to take place and has been postponed. READ: COVID-19: NCC taking heat, decisions to be challenged New dates and times are still to be communicated yet. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.